summary: This is an FBI 302 interview report documenting an attempted interview at a witness's residence on July 6, 2019. The witness, upon learning the agents were from the FBI, immediately stated 'JEFFREY EPSTEIN' as the reason for their visit, invoked her right to counsel, and was served a Grand Jury Subpoena. The interview was terminated.

persons.name: Joseph E Nascimento
persons.context: Identified by the witness as her counsel. He is an attorney with the Ross Amsel, Raben and Nascimento Law Firm.

persons.name: Jeffrey Epstein
persons.context: The witness immediately stated his name as the presumed reason for the FBI's visit to her residence.

connections.description: Nascimento is identified as the attorney for a witness who was being questioned in relation to the Jeffrey Epstein investigation.

events.title: FBI Attempted Interview at Witness Residence
events.description: FBI agents and a Task Force Officer attempted to interview a witness at her residence. The witness invoked her right to counsel upon hearing the agents were from the FBI and mentioned Jeffrey Epstein.

events.title: Grand Jury Subpoena Served
events.description: A Grand Jury Subpoena was served to the witness at her residence in connection with a federal investigation.

keyFacts: A witness, upon being contacted by FBI agents, immediately stated 'JEFFREY EPSTEIN' as the presumed reason for the investigation.
The witness invoked her right to counsel, identifying Joseph E Nascimento as her attorney, which led to the immediate termination of the interview.
The witness was served a Grand Jury Subpoena on July 6, 2019, in Miami, Florida.
The document is an FBI 302 report, dated July 18, 2019, documenting the events of July 6, 2019.
